         Review: remove once Spring Security publishes a fix and dependency is upgraded. -->
    <suppress until="2026-07-19">
        <notes><![CDATA[
        CVE-2026-22732: Spring Security BCryptPasswordEncoder timing side-channel (CVSS 9.1).
        No verified fix in spring-security-crypto <= 6.5.9 (latest as of 2026-04-19).
        ]]></notes>
        <cve>CVE-2026-22732</cve>
    </suppress>

    <!-- NO FIX AVAILABLE: CVE-2026-24400 — XXE injection in AssertJ XmlAssert when parsing
         attacker-controlled XML. CVSS v3: 8.2; CVSS v4 environmental score triggers the 9.0
         build threshold. Affects assertj-core up to 3.27.0 (latest on Maven Central).
         assertj-core is TEST SCOPE ONLY — never shipped in any final artifact.
         Runtime exposure is zero; this CVE is unreachable from production code.
         Review: remove once assertj publishes a fix. -->
    <suppress until="2026-07-19">
        <notes><![CDATA[
        CVE-2026-24400: AssertJ XmlAssert XXE injection. CVSS v3 8.2 / v4 >= 9.0.
        assertj-core is test-scope only — not present in any shipped artifact.
        No fix in assertj-core <= 3.27.0 (latest as of 2026-04-19).
        ]]></notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/org\.assertj/assertj-core@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2026-24400</cve>
    </suppress>

</suppressions>
